  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Recent experimental and clinical studies have shown that platelets play a critical role in
      liver ischemia and regeneration. Thrombocytopenia, a frequent and potentially serious
      condition in liver transplantation (LT) recipients, was shown to be associated with
      postoperative morbidity and mortality after partial hepatectomy.

      The investigators aim at evaluating whether postoperative low platelet counts are indicators
      of short- and long-term outcomes after liver transplantation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
